5|$|Comparisons of KOI 072.02 to the 1235 other Kepler Objects of Interest in Kepler's {{field of}} vision allowed <b>astronomers</b> <b>to</b> use models {{that led to the}} {{confirmation}} of KOI 072.02 as a planet {{with a high degree of}} certainty. KOI 072.02 was then renamed Kepler-10c. The planet's confirmation was announced at the Boston meeting of the American Astronomical Society on May 23, 2011.|$|E
5|$|Elemental abundances in the {{photosphere}} {{are well}} known from spectroscopic studies, but {{the composition of the}} interior of the Sun is more poorly understood. A solar wind sample return mission, Genesis, was designed to allow <b>astronomers</b> <b>to</b> directly measure the composition of solar material.|$|E
